section.para:
    	PortalLayout is a simple component that implements HasComponents interface.
    	It wraps other comonents in Portlets and renders them in a stack. In order to add a component to 
    	PortalLayout one should call the following:  


private void createPortal() {
   ....
   final PortalLayout portalLayout = new PortalLayout();
   ....
   Component childComponent = new TextArea();
   Portlet portlet = portalLayout.wrapInPortlet(childComponent);
   ....
}

    	The Portlet is a child class of an AbstractExtension. On the client-side it is responsible for 
    	providing a chrome for a wrapped component: draggable area (header), caption and icon areas, controls for close/collapse and auxillary components
    	in the header that play a role of toolbars. Portlet provides basic setter/getter methods on the server-side:


public void setCollapsed(boolean collapsed) {}

public void setClosable(boolean closable) {}

public void setCollapsible(boolean collapsible) {}

public void setLocked(boolean locked) {}

public boolean isLocked() {}

public boolean isCollapsed() {}

public boolean isCollapsible() {}

public boolean isClosable() {}
